Here are some areas in which departments might promote readiness among faculty. These are offered as examples, not recommendations.
It's important to engage your chair/director/faculty leader in completing this page.

<ul>
<li>Promote/ensure computer backup.</li>

<li>Safeguard research materials.</li>

<li>Encourage physicians to determine standard-of-care considerations for austere conditions.</li>

<li>Encourage faculty to prepare to deliver courses in alternate ways if classrooms are not available.</li>

<li>Involve physicians in disaster drills.</li>

<li>Educate medical faculty on the emergency operations plan.</li>

<li>Encourage/assist Principal Investigators to train lab staff in disaster issues.</li>

<li>Encourage Principal Investigators to devise plans to cope with refrigeration failure.</li>

<li>Encourage faculty to insist that equipment in labs &amp; clinics be secured against earthquake.</li>

</ul>
